Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Add --depth as primary option, keep --report-depth as
 deprecated alias

- Add '--depth' as the primary CLI option for setting markdown header depth
- Keep '--report-depth' as a backwards-compatible alias (deprecated)
- Update help text and documentation to show '--depth' as primary
- Make Validation.cs PrintValidationHeader respect context.ReportDepth
- Add unit tests for '--depth' in ContextTests, ValidationTests, ProgramTests
- Add integration tests for '--depth' error cases
- Add SonarMark-Validation-Depth requirement with test coverage
- Update requirements traceability in program.yaml, validation.yaml, self-test.yaml

Co-authored-by: Malcolmnixon <1863707+Malcolmnixon@users.noreply.github.com>
